    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-10-15T12:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-09-17T05:35:00-05:00" n="51"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d51">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">511.4 A 2/110: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Secretary General of the League of Nations</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Drummond</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName> [<date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1924-10-15T12:36:00-05:00"
                            notBefore="1924-09-17T14:00:00+03:25">
                            <hi rend="italic">undated</hi>
                        </date>].<lb/>[Received October 15, 1924—12:36 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Reference my letter C. L. 5, 14th January, 1924. Would remind you no reply yet
                    received. Answer would facilitate preliminary arrangements conference.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Drummond</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
